Yesterday when we were out running errands my son told me,
&ldquo;Mom, I am going to be really good at nap time today.&rdquo;
I was in the midst of trying to find the things on my mental list and push the cart with three kids on it, so I muttered something like, &ldquo;good honey&rdquo; and continued on. My son was so excited because after nap time we were going to plant flowers in our yard.
